	<Usage>held in 1 hand</Usage>
	<Description>Many books and spellbooks are treated in this wax formula to protect them from the elements, but &lt;i&gt;waterproofing wax's&lt;/i&gt; liquid-repellent properties can be further applied to split up a &lt;i&gt;grease&lt;/i&gt; spell into useful smaller sections. When the spell is cast in an area while using this catalyst, the conjured grease fills three 5-foot squares within 30 feet instead of its normal area; these squares don't need to be contiguous.</Description>
</Item>
